Croatia’s INA, HEP May Gain Dioki Shares in Swap, Poslovni Says

-- B y   J a s m i n a   K u z m a n o v i c
-- 
2011-07-25T09:58:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-25/croatia-s-ina-hep-may-gain-dioki-shares-in-swap-poslovni-says.html
Croatia  is arranging a debt-for-
equity swap that would leave  INA  Industrija Nafte d.d., power
board Hrvatska Elektroprivreda d.d., and creditor banks with
shares in Dioki d.d,  Poslovni Dnevnik  reported today, citing
people it didn’t identify.  The chemical manufacturer Dioki owes 65 million kuna ($12
million) to INA and 160 million kuna to the national power
board, according to the Zagreb-based business newspaper.
Dioki, which owns chemical facility Dina-Petrokemija d.d. on
the island of Krk, also owes millions of kuna to local banks,
the newspaper said.  The debt deal is being arranged by the  Economy Ministry ,
Poslovni reported, without saying how it got the information.
The government owns 44.84 percent of INA’s stock, while
 Hungary ’s Mol Nyrt has 47.47 percent of the company’s shares,
in addition to management rights in Croatia’s largest refiner.  To contact the reporter responsible for the story:
Jasmina Kuzmanovic in Zagreb at 
 jkuzmanovic@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for the story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net  